Class eRadio

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dv8tion.jda.hooks.ListenerAdapter
      • net.grasinga.discord.bots.eRadio
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.dv8tion.jda.hooks.EventListener

    public class eRadio
extends net.dv8tion.jda.hooks.ListenerAdapter
    Ethereal Network's Radio Bot
    eRadio is a bot the plays an internet radio station on discord.
    Plays the given radio station in the given voice channel.
    Arguments can be passed in through the command line or from a bot.properties file.
    bot.properties file should have one argument per line.

    Arguments are as follows:
    - Bot Token
    - Radio Station URL
    - VoiceChannel

    Created by Grasinga using JDA and JDA-Player

      • joinVoice

        private void joinVoice(net.dv8tion.jda.entities.Guild guild,
                       net.dv8tion.jda.entities.TextChannel channel,
                       java.lang.String chanName)
        Function runs after the '-join' command is entered. Places the bot in the VoiceChannel specified by chanName argument if possible. If the VoiceChannel cannot be joined because it doesn't exist, a message is sent to channel to notify the user of the command.
        Parameters:
        guild - Used to get the current guild where the Exception occurred.
        channel - Used to get the channel of the command that caused the Exception.
        chanName - VoiceChannel to join.
